# 2026-03-18 22:28:46.809918
+Keep the current working version and evolve it into version 0.1 without breaking the app.
+
+Create a clearer and more usable UI and improve the analysis design.
+
+Goals for version 0.1:
+- keep the app launching successfully
+- keep Start Session / Stop Session working
+- improve the menu and interaction flow so it is clear how to use the app
+- add a basic explanation inside the UI of what the app measures and how to use it
+- design a simple but realistic aim/mouse analysis approach
+- save local session data
+- mark this release as version 0.1
+
+Please do this step by step:
+
+1. App versioning
+- Add visible version text: "v0.1"
+- Show it in the main window title or inside the UI
+
+2. Better menu / interaction flow
+- Add a clearer top area or side menu with sections such as:
+  - Home
+  - Session
+  - Analysis
+  - History
+  - Settings
+- If a full menu is too much, create a simple tab-like layout or section buttons
+- Make it obvious what the user should do first
+
+3. Better UX for aim/mouse interaction
+- Add a short help/info block in the UI:
+  - what Start Session does
+  - what Stop Session does
+  - what is being measured
+  - that this is passive local analysis only
+- Show the currently selected mode / game / genre clearly
+- Add visible status labels:
+  - Idle
+  - Recording
+  - Analyzing
+  - Session saved
+
+4. Real session model
+- When Start Session is pressed:
+  - create a session id
+  - store start time
+  - set state to Recording
+- When Stop Session is pressed:
+  - store end time
+  - compute duration
+  - set state to Analyzing briefly
+  - save session data locally
+  - then return to Idle or Session saved
+
+5. Basic local storage
+- Save sessions to a local JSON file
+- Each session should include at least:
+  - session_id
+  - selected game/genre
+  - start_time
+  - end_time
+  - duration_seconds
+  - basic counters/metrics
+- Keep the storage simple and readable
+
+6. Basic analysis design for version 0.1
+Implement a small, believable first-pass analysis model based only on safe local behavior.
+Do not fake advanced ML.
+
+For version 0.1, calculate simple metrics such as:
+- session duration
+- number of clicks
+- estimated movement activity
+- average movement magnitude
+- movement variability / jitter estimate
+- simple intensity score
+- simple stability score
+
+Then show a few interpretation labels such as:
+- low activity / medium activity / high activity
+- stable / slightly jittery / very jittery
+- calm movement / aggressive movement
+
+7. Small dashboard for v0.1
+Add a simple overview area that displays:
+- current selected game/genre
+- current status
+- last session id
+- last session duration
+- basic metrics from the most recent session
+- 2-4 short recommendations
+
+8. Recommendations for v0.1
+Keep them simple and honest.
+Examples:
+- movement looks stable
+- movement seems jittery
+- session was too short for strong conclusions
+- try recording a longer session
+- click activity was low
+- movement intensity was high
+
+9. Safety text
+In the UI or Settings, show a short note:
+- passive local analysis only
+- no game memory reading
+- no injection
+- no input emulation
+
+10. Code quality
+- Keep the current working version
+- Improve incrementally
+- Do not rewrite everything from scratch unless necessary
+- Fix only the issues needed for v0.1
+- Keep PySide6
+- Replace app.exec_() with app.exec()
+
+11. Final output
+After making the changes:
+- run the app again
+- confirm it still launches
+- summarize what was added for version 0.1
+- list any remaining limitations for the next version
+
+Important:
+Do not break the current working version.
+Work incrementally on top of it.
+If an error appears, fix only that exact error and rerun.

